==English==
===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/pæn'deɪ'ĭsts}}

===Alternative spellings===
*sometimes hyphenated or expressed as a phrase: '''pan-deists''', '''pan deists'''
*sometimes either the P or both the P and D are capitalized: '''Pandeists''', '''PanDeists'''
*variations of capitalization and spacing may be combined: '''Pan-deists''', '''Pan-Deists''', '''Pan Deists''', '''Pan deists'''
===Noun===
'''pandeists'''
# plural of [[pandeist]], one who believes in [[pandeism]]
#:''[Y]ou are part of God, like it or not, from the viewpoint of those who are '''pandeists''' or pantheists.''[http://www.volconvo.com/forums/showthread.php?t=4942&page=2&pp=10]
#:''[Y]ou seem to be drawing a strict distinction between God and the universe. Not all Deists do this, so for these "'''PanDeists'''" the point becomes moot.'' [http://www.beliefnet.com/boards/message_list.asp?boardID=36669&discussionID=512713]
#:''[M]any panentheists are actually panendeists, many process theists are actually process deists, many scientific pantheists are actually '''pandeists''', etc.'' [http://dynamicdeism.org/forum/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=170&]




